<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1778,2019]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,1778,1803]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Recognition</emphasis>
. This species is distinguished by palpus and antenna brown; postpedicel nearly as long as wide; fore tarsi yellow; dorsocentrals arranged in 
<number box="[639,681,1814,1838]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
irregular rows.
</paragraph>
